We did some of this at our worship night.

19:29.428 --> 19:30.610
We anointed with oil.

19:33.794 --> 19:38.360
Some would say that this text is meaning medicinal, and they would put oil on wounds.

19:39.381 --> 19:40.663
And I think there's some truth to that.

19:41.504 --> 19:43.086
I'm not denying that interpretation.

19:44.108 --> 19:45.630
But I think it's beyond that.

19:46.751 --> 19:59.088
And I think that when we anoint people with oil, we're identifying that person as having the blessing of God on them, that the power of God is then coming on them and in them to do what?

20:00.189 --> 20:03.634
Possibly to heal your body, to heal your mind,

20:04.418 --> 20:05.699
to heal your relationship.

20:06.600 --> 20:06.981
Don't know.

20:08.182 --> 20:11.186
But the anointing is important even to this day.

20:11.866 --> 20:12.928
It means to consecrate.

20:13.588 --> 20:15.691
That means you are going to get anointed with oil.

20:16.211 --> 20:18.093
You're going to get baptized with the Spirit.

20:19.996 --> 20:25.181
David says that in the text, you anoint my head with oil and my cup is overflowing.

20:26.783 --> 20:29.526
This point, receive the anointing God promises.

20:30.067 --> 20:32.850
Notice, 1 John 2, 27 is on the screen.

20:33.122 --> 20:34.463
I'll show you this verse as well.

20:35.444 --> 20:41.450
But the anointing that you received from him abides in you, referring to who?

20:42.891 --> 20:43.171
Anybody?

20:44.333 --> 20:48.076
Holy Spirit, you have no need that anyone should teach you.

20:49.017 --> 20:56.644
But as his anointing teaches you about everything and is true and is no lie, just as has taught you, abide in him.

20:57.645 --> 20:59.927
This relationship with the Holy Spirit is so important.

21:00.808 --> 21:02.770
Can I just ask you, do you know the Holy Spirit?

21:03.970 --> 21:07.815
I'm not gonna ask you if you know the Father, although you should.

21:09.017 --> 21:12.441
I'm not gonna ask you if you know the Son of God, although you should.

21:13.703 --> 21:18.590
I'm gonna ask you personally, and specifically, who is the Holy Spirit to you?

21:19.852 --> 21:20.472
Do you know Him?

21:21.414 --> 21:22.255
Do you walk with Him?

21:22.816 --> 21:23.797
Do you listen to Him?

21:24.217 --> 21:25.199
Are you filled by Him?

21:25.719 --> 21:27.081
Are you anointed by Him?

21:27.542 --> 21:28.824
Do you have the unction of God?

21:29.284 --> 21:32.389
Is God's hand on your life?

21:32.629 --> 21:33.490
Can you say yes?

21:34.082 --> 21:34.703
Do you believe that?

21:35.624 --> 21:36.906
I'm going to tell you, you're going to need that.

21:39.009 --> 21:39.991
You're going to need to know that.

21:42.014 --> 21:43.136
This anointing is for you.

21:44.938 --> 21:45.740
It's for all of us.

21:47.302 --> 21:48.624
Can I show you Psalm 92?

21:49.045 --> 21:49.706
Go there with me.

21:49.726 --> 21:50.507
It's not on the screen.

21:51.028 --> 21:51.849
I want to show it to you.

21:51.889 --> 21:52.570
Psalm 92.

21:55.795 --> 21:57.137
Notice what the writer says here.

21:57.157 --> 22:03.186
92 verse 9.

22:07.746 --> 22:12.510
For behold, your enemies, oh Lord, for behold, your enemies shall perish.

22:12.931 --> 22:14.532
All evil doers shall be scattered.

22:16.394 --> 22:19.357
But you have exalted my horn like that of the wild ox.

22:20.438 --> 22:23.080
And you have poured over me fresh oil.

22:26.243 --> 22:27.765
I don't know about you, but that encourages me.

22:29.106 --> 22:31.448
You're saying, how does that encourage you, Chris?

22:31.468 --> 22:35.692
Because constantly in my Christian life, I need God to pour fresh oil.

22:35.752 --> 22:36.313
What's that mean?

22:36.633 --> 22:37.554
Fresh onion.

22:38.018 --> 22:41.963
fresh baptism, fresh feeling, fresh power.

22:43.725 --> 22:46.369
God, would you pour over me that fresh oil?

22:50.213 --> 22:50.934
This anointing.

22:51.876 --> 22:57.783
When adversaries and adversity come into your life, this anointing or blessing is promised to you.

22:57.923 --> 23:00.026
No weapon formed against you will what?

23:00.206 --> 23:01.588
What's the Bible saying?

23:01.608 --> 23:02.108
Prosper.

23:04.111 --> 23:06.514
This includes the enemies, his devices,

23:06.658 --> 23:12.786
tactics and wily ways, receive the anointing, be receptive to his spirit this morning.

23:16.430 --> 23:19.014
He's wanting to pour this fresh oil on your head this morning.

23:19.754 --> 23:23.739
Seriously application in your outline, thank the Lord for his blessing.

23:24.901 --> 23:26.303
Thank the Lord for his blessing.

23:27.304 --> 23:28.986
David said, my cup does what?

23:30.148 --> 23:30.888
It overflows.

23:31.409 --> 23:32.791
Can I just illustrate that for you?

23:32.811 --> 23:35.314
I want to illustrate that for you.

23:35.746 --> 23:37.008
with this pitcher of water.

23:38.009 --> 23:39.932
And this is going to represent the Holy Spirit.

23:40.553 --> 23:42.316
And this jar is going to represent us.

23:43.337 --> 23:49.106
Now, typically when you are pouring something into a glass, you might want to be paying attention, right?

23:49.146 --> 23:55.455
Because if you're not, then it can spill over on your countertop, onto the floor.

23:55.475 --> 23:56.457
You ever had that happen before?

23:56.937 --> 23:58.840
And you're like, oh, man, I wasn't paying attention.

23:59.441 --> 24:00.603
You get a little bit frustrated.

24:00.963 --> 24:02.866
It's a little bit chaotic in the house, maybe.

24:03.874 --> 24:08.120
But I want to illustrate this using it with what David is saying in the text.

24:08.841 --> 24:10.824
He said, my cup is overflowing.

24:11.785 --> 24:15.871
And so it's like, oh God, would you just pour into me the Holy Spirit?

24:16.832 --> 24:19.136
Would you just fill me all the way to the top?

24:20.177 --> 24:24.864
And then when it gets all the way to the top, then your light feels a little bit uncomfortable.

24:24.884 --> 24:26.566
And you're like, oh no, I need to stop this.

24:26.626 --> 24:28.309
I need to clean this up.

24:28.329 --> 24:29.330
I can't have this happen.

24:29.550 --> 24:30.972
This is out of my comfort zone.

24:30.992 --> 24:32.114
What do I do about this?

24:32.930 --> 24:33.931
This is a lot of Christians.

24:35.593 --> 24:42.660
God is wanting to overflow your life so much and you're saying, no, God, I need you to stop it now.

24:43.661 --> 24:46.023
God, I don't even know if I can handle all of this.

24:47.284 --> 24:49.787
I don't know if I was raised in this tradition or not.

24:53.470 --> 24:56.213
When God starts to overflow your life, receive that.

24:56.754 --> 25:01.138
When he starts to anoint your life and bless your life in abundance,

25:02.114 --> 25:07.881
Don't get to the place where you're trying to clean everything up and understand it completely because you're not going to be able to do that.

25:08.842 --> 25:09.743
Just receive it.

25:10.564 --> 25:11.825
Just go, God, I want more.

25:12.546 --> 25:16.731
I want you to overflow my life because this is what you want to do in my life.

25:18.013 --> 25:18.894
Does that make any sense?

25:20.836 --> 25:21.737
There's so much more.

25:22.959 --> 25:25.081
I didn't realize this early on in my Christian life.

25:25.982 --> 25:29.266
There's so much more that God has for us.

25:32.450 --> 25:34.433
David uses an interesting word for God.

25:34.453 --> 25:42.147
He calls God Jehovah Nissi, the one who fights for me while I feast, the one who fights for me.

25:42.587 --> 25:45.533
I'm going to give you another illustration that I'm going to close.

25:45.553 --> 25:52.144
Here's a picture, and if you've ever been to Boston Garden, you'll go in there and of course the banners are over top.

25:53.626 --> 25:58.034
Can you imagine the adversary, but let me use it in the sports analogy, opponent

25:58.306 --> 26:06.418
The opponent comes in the Boston Garden and they see all the banners up there, like those, championships, world championship, one after the other.

26:06.739 --> 26:10.384
What do you think is going into the mind of the opponent or the adversary?

26:12.187 --> 26:16.613
Jehovah Nissi, you're fellowshipping with God at the table.

26:17.595 --> 26:19.277
He is Jehovah Nissi over us.

26:19.317 --> 26:20.139
He's our banner.

26:21.280 --> 26:27.730
And when the enemy comes in to your life to try to bring in strongholds or try to do something against you, adversity,

26:28.066 --> 26:30.609
Don't you know that God is over at all?

26:31.751 --> 26:34.254
That the enemy looks at the banners and goes, uh-oh.

26:34.635 --> 26:37.659
So that means you could have your hot dog and your coke and just sit there and chill out.

26:39.301 --> 26:41.484
Seriously, he's called you to a table.

26:42.105 --> 26:43.046
That's what David's saying.

26:43.487 --> 26:47.312
You prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies.

26:47.332 --> 26:48.874
In other words, I'm in communion with God.

26:49.254 --> 26:50.296
I'm fellowshiping with God.

26:50.696 --> 26:52.038
I'm having these moments with God.

26:52.319 --> 26:53.600
The unction of God is on me.

26:53.640 --> 26:54.982
The anointing of God is on me.

26:55.343 --> 26:56.805
My adversary is watching that.

26:56.845 --> 26:57.906
The devil included.

26:58.178 --> 26:59.800
And he sees Jehovah Nissi.

27:00.321 --> 27:05.908
He sees the banner over you, a victory, of a conqueror in Christ.

27:07.149 --> 27:08.371
This is where David's going with that.

27:10.473 --> 27:11.715
And he's saying it to us as well.

27:13.177 --> 27:16.882
Would you rely not on your own ability?

27:18.904 --> 27:26.834
Would you receive the anointing and you'll overcome any adversary or adversity?

27:28.002 --> 27:29.805
Hallelujah and amen.

27:30.406 --> 27:30.966
That is the word.

27:30.987 --> 27:33.230
Look, can we read the Psalm together all out loud?

27:33.250 --> 27:35.073
Psalm 23, we've been trying to memorize it.

27:35.774 --> 27:36.875
We'll do that all together.

27:36.956 --> 27:37.176
Ready?

27:38.177 --> 27:39.299
The Lord is my shepherd.

27:39.880 --> 27:40.942
I shall not want.

27:41.242 --> 27:43.405
He makes me lie down in green pastures.

27:44.006 --> 27:45.909
He leads me beside still waters.

27:46.210 --> 27:47.491
He restores my soul.

27:48.173 --> 27:51.237
He leads me in paths of righteousness for his namesake.

27:51.798 --> 27:57.106
Even though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil for you are with me.

27:57.346 --> 27:59.529
Your rod and your staff, they comfort me.

28:00.010 --> 28:02.974
You prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies.

28:03.515 --> 28:06.700
You anoint my head with oil, my cup overflows.

28:07.320 --> 28:14.451
Surely goodness and mercy shall follow me all the days of my life, and I shall dwell in the house of the Lord forever.

28:14.811 --> 28:15.893
This is the word of the Lord.

28:16.273 --> 28:16.754
You are loved.

28:20.940 --> 28:24.946
Thanks for listening to the Crossway Christian Church's Milford Campus Sermon podcast.

28:25.122 --> 28:32.366
If you like to plug into the life of our community or have any questions that we might be able to answer, visit our website at crosswayscc.org to connect with us.

28:32.828 --> 28:34.092
Until next time, we can be with you.

28:34.413 --> 28:36.018
May the Lord bless you and keep you.

